answers.body_markdown:
No. That is not a valid syntax in Java. 

You could do this though:

    Object[] arr = new Object[] {
        new Integer(1), 
        new Integer(2),
        new Object[] {
            new Integer(3),
            new Integer(4),
            new Object[] {
                new Integer(5)
            }
        },
        new Integer(6)
    };

In python you can do:

    arr = [1, 2, [3,4,[5]],6];

In JavaScript:

    let arr = [1, 2, [3,4,[5]],6];
